subsection.def:
statutes
                    (規程) means the statutes of the
                University;

paragraph.content:
to provide such lectures and instruction for persons not members of the
                University as the University may determine, and to grant certificates to such
                persons;

shall discharge such duties as are specified in the Ordinance and
                        statutes and such other duties as may be determined by the
                        Council;

the Chancellor, the Pro-Chancellor, the Vice-Chancellor, the Deputy
                        Vice-Chancellor, the Pro-Vice-Chancellors and the Treasurer;
                            (Amended G.N.A. 59 of 1960; L.N. 69 of 1968; L.N. 159 of 1970; L.N. 167 of 1992)

the Chairman, Deputy Chairman and Clerk of Convocation;
                            (Replaced L.N. 15 of 1973. Amended L.N. 186 of
                        2003)

subsection.content:
7 persons, not being students or employees of the University, appointed
                        by the Chancellor, one of whom shall be appointed the Chairman by the
                        Chancellor;

paragraph.content:
to purchase, grant, sell, convey, assign, surrender, and yield up,
                        exchange, partition, mortgage, demise, reassign, transfer, and accept leases
                        of real and personal property on behalf of the University;

to incorporate or set up a unit trust and appoint trustees thereof;
                            (Added L.N. 72 of
                            1993)

to give directions to the Senate or to any officer or teacher of the
                        University in any financial matter or any matter affecting the property of
                        the University;

to prescribe the duties of officers, teachers, and other employees whom
                        it may appoint and to fix their remuneration and the terms and conditions of
                        their appointments;

the prescribing of anything which is by the Ordinance or the
                            statutes to be prescribed by regulations made by the Council;
                            and

to determine what examinations and courses of study in other
                        Universities or places of learning shall be deemed equivalent to
                        examinations and courses of study in the University;

to fix the time, mode and conditions of competition for, and to award
                        fellowships, scholarships, and other educational endowments and prizes in
                        accordance with the terms thereof;

to elect a Chairman, who shall hold office for such period as
                        Convocation may determine and who shall in the absence of the Chancellor
                        preside at its meetings;

to report its proceedings to the Court, the Council or the Senate;
                            (Replaced L.N. 15 of
                            1973)

section.def:
student panel (學生小組) means the panel appointed under paragraph
                    4;
                        (Amended L.N. 112 of 2023)

paragraph.content:
an offence in connection with degree, diploma, or certificate
                            examinations, including violation of any of the regulations of the
                            Senate governing conduct at examinations or otherwise;

refusal or failure to attend upon or comply with any summons before
                            or order of or decision made by the Committee or by the Vice-Chancellor
                            in exercise of his disciplinary powers or by the Council;

subparagraph.content:
is disrupting teaching, study, research or the administration
                                of the University;
                                    (Amended L.N. 112 of 2023)

paragraph.content:
fine (maximum to be determined from time to time by the Council);
                                (Replaced L.N. 123 of
                                    1994)

withdrawal of any academic or other University privilege, benefit,
                            right to facility other than the right to follow courses of instruction
                            and present himself for examinations;
